node.title: NT records nine new COVID-19 cases overnight
node.description: The Northern Territory records nine new cases of coronavirus overnight, bringing the total number of cases in the Katherine and Robinson River outbreak announced yesterdayÂ to 11.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded\u00a0nine new COVID-19 cases\u00a0overnight, bringing the total number of cases in the Katherine and Robinson River outbreak announced yesterday\u00a0to 11.\u00a0", "Chief Minister Michael Gunner said all the new cases were\u00a0Aboriginal people and household contacts of the two cases confirmed yesterday.", "One of them, a 65-year-old woman, has been admitted to Royal Darwin Hospital.", "More to come."]
